          <p class='first-para'>
            I want to interject that the idea of a committee of that nature consisting of only five&#x2014;I know that the provision says, "at least five"&#x2014;is, as the noble Lord said, too small. The problems experienced by any committee on which I have served in trying to get a quorum mean that we will need a bigger group. Let us use your Lordships' House as an example. If we employ people who are very important at doing other work, they tend to get taken off to do other things. Getting the right number of people together would be difficult. I hope that the Minister will assure us that a body consisting of only five people would never be considered.
          </p>
